<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title><%= title %></title>

      <meta charset="utf-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
      <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style2.css' />
      <link href="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
      <script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"></script>
      <script src="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.0/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

  </head>
  <body>

  <div id="wrapper">
    <div class="overlay"></div>

    <% include templates/sidebar.ejs %>

    <!-- Page Content -->
    <div id="page-content-wrapper">
      <button type="button" class="hamburger is-closed" data-toggle="offcanvas">
        <span class="hamb-top"></span>
        <span class="hamb-middle"></span>
        <span class="hamb-bottom"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="col-xs-1"></div>
        <div class="col-xs-10">
          <h1><%= title %></h1>

          <br>

          <div class="col-xs-6">
            <h2>Introduction of Web Pages</h2>
            <font size="4">
              <h3>Dashboard</h3>
              <p>
                Dashboard web page is the monitor for all active tables in PlASH RethinkDB.
                Users can inspect every table's dynamic line chart, the latest update time
                and its next update estimation, period and so on.
                Statistics tab provides the information about
                the distribution of the storage for all databases and tables.
              </p>
              <h3>RethinkDB Configuration</h3>
              <p>
                There is data visualization (Collapsible Tree) in this page.
                Users can realize the whole structure of current RethinkDB
                including databases, tables and nested attributes.
                This visualization is not static but updating with current RethinkDB.
              </p>
              <h3>Data Query and Download Service</h3>
              <p>
                Instead of obtaining data by commands, users can use the user interface
                to decide data of database/tables from single or all devices in a specific time.
                The output format is only JSON file. We will offer other file formats in the future.
              </p>

              <h3>Notification system by e-mail (backend)</h3>
              <p>
                Web administrators will get notification as one table's data flow malfunctions. That is,
                ODD website is checking active tables all the time.
                When one table is not updated for a long time set by administrators,
                an e-mail will be sent from the server's backend.
              </p>
              <h3>Notification system (Slack website) (backend)</h3>
              <p>
                Coming Soon...
              </p>
              <br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

            </font>

          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-1"></div>






        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-1"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /#page-content-wrapper -->

  </div>
  <!-- /#wrapper -->

  <script type="text/javascript" src="javascripts/test_template.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
